# Modern Project Rules Example
# This shows the new recommended approach using .cursor/rules

[Always]
You are assisting with an educational project for barefoot developers.
Focus on clarity, simplicity, and learning value in all code generation.

[Code Style]
- Use 2-space indentation
- Prefer const/let over var
- Use template literals for string concatenation
- Add explanatory comments for learning purposes
- Keep line length under 80 characters

[Architecture]
- Start with working minimal examples
- Use progressive enhancement
- Separate concerns (HTML structure, CSS styling, JS behavior)
- Implement local-first data storage
- Handle errors gracefully with user-friendly messages

[Security]
- Never expose API keys in frontend code
- Always validate user input
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Implement proper CORS handling
- Sanitize dynamic content before display

[Educational Focus]
- Every code example should teach a concept
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Include alternative approaches where relevant
- Add links to documentation for further learning
- Show both the simple and advanced ways

[Testing]
- Include console.log statements for debugging
- Create manual test scenarios
- Test offline functionality
- Verify mobile responsiveness
- Check accessibility features

[Auto Attached]
When working on HTML files:
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Include proper meta tags
- Add ARIA labels for accessibility
- Structure content logically

When working on CSS files:
- Use CSS custom properties
- Implement mobile-first design
- Include vendor prefixes where needed
- Comment complex selectors

When working on JavaScript files:
- Use modern ES6+ syntax
- Implement proper error handling
- Add JSDoc comments
- Follow functional programming principles where appropriate